This paper deals with dynamic routing policies for wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of time-varying cost factors, which is a concept related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the minimization of network delay, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The use of a fluid limit to study wireless networks is a concept related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a Pareto optimal tradeoff, which is a concept related to decision making (cs.DC).
